parameters: Clea: This is quite a unique place, isn't it?

Mage Relm: This is an empire, but it's not really like the
empire, so there are still many uncivilized people who
haven't adapted to the empire here.

Thief Nora: There's a rather unique smell here, isn't there?
It's kind of animalistic... I can smell strong blood and the
scent of iron.

Priest Sophia: The Valt region is a rather unique place that
has had two wars with the empire in the past. It has
produced many mercenaries and is quite a special place.

Priest Sophia: Hehe, it's funny how life can bring us
opportunities like this, stepping into a place like this.
Clea: Let's go meet Chief Goat-san.

Mage Relm: This is an empire, but it's not really like the
empire, so there are still many uncivilized people who
haven't adapted to the empire here.

Thief Nora: There's a rather unique smell here, isn't there?
It's almost animalistic... I can smell strong blood and the
scent of iron.

Priestess Sophia: The Valto region is a rather unique place
that has had two wars with the empire in the past. It has
produced many mercenaries and is quite a special place.

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, it's funny how life can bring us
opportunities like this, stepping into a place like this.
Clea: Let's go meet Chief Goat-san.

Priestess Sophia: Goat-san, you didn't mention anything
important, did you...?
Clea: Indeed, I didn't ask why humans become ogres.

Priestess Sophia: I wonder if it's not that I didn't talk,
but rather that I couldn't talk...?

Warrior of the Bulk Brigade: As a proud warrior of the Bulk
Brigade, I have been chosen to go to Fotizona as a security
guard, and I intend to fulfill my duty.

Bulk Brigade Warrior: As a proud warrior of the Bulk
Brigade, who has been chosen to go to Fotizona as a security
guard, I intend to fulfill my duty.

Bulk Corps Warrior: This is the Empire, but it is not the
Empire! It is a place where the proud warriors of Vald live.

Warrior of the Bulk Brigade: This is the Empire, yet it is
not the Empire! It is a place where the proud warriors of
Vald live.

Traveling peddler: This is an interesting place, you'll
often be amazed by its unique culture.

Traveling peddler: This is an interesting place, you'll
often be amazed by its unique culture.

Female Beer Craftsman: Brewing beer is a woman's job in
Vald. Skilled women like me often receive approaches from
gentlemen.

Female Beer Craftsman: Brewing beer is a woman's job in
Valt. Skilled women like me often receive approaches from
gentlemen.

Male Hunter: Some of our prey may seem savage as they are
offered to the goddess Actina, but it is the form of our
prayers.

Male Hunter: Some of our prey may seem savage as they are
offered to the goddess Actina, but it is the form of our
prayers.

Bulk Corps Warrior: Have you ever been to the arena? I'd
like to participate someday for a test of strength.

Bulk Corps Warrior: Have you ever been to the arena? I'd
like to participate someday for a test of strength.

Pharmacist Saliva: Did you come here seeking medicinal
herbs? The forest that Goddess Actina has bestowed upon us
is a natural medicine cabinet.

Clea: May I ask you to tell me the location of the Oradoru's
Eye?

Pharmacist Saliva: I've heard it from everyone in the Bulk
Gang. If you're recognized as a warrior by them, I can tell
you the location.

Pharmacist Saliva: However, finding and defeating it is your
job.

Pharmacist Saliva: There is a special bat that favors the
Oradoru's Eye. If you think about it the other way around,
if you find the bat, it means there are medicinal herbs.

Pharmacist Saliva: It's better to be prepared. These bats
have the power to paralyze humans.

Pharmacist Saliva: I'll guide you nearby, so come with me to
the depths of the forest!

Pharmacist Saliva: As expected of a warrior recognized by
the Bulk Corps!
Clea: Thank you for your assistance in slaying the dragon.

Goat of the Bulk Brigade: Hahaha, I should be the one
thanking you! I'm proud to have been able to be on the front
lines!
Goat of the Bulk Brigade: Is something the matter today?

Priestess Sophia: I would like to request some lumber for
construction purposes.

Goat of the Bulk Brigade: Hahaha, no need to hold back, take
the usable lumber with you.

Goat of the Bulk Brigade: However, I expect you to provide
reinforcements! Please cut some lumber at the hunting
grounds of the Bulk Brigade!
Clea: Understood, leave it to me.

Goat of the Bulk Brigade: Hahaha, I believe we will be able
to finish it safely!

Senior warrior of the Bulk Brigade: 'Warriors, I have heard
the story from Lord Goat.'

Senior warrior of the Bulk Brigade: 'Lord Goat has entered
the Forest of Tranquility, our sacred place, while
considering the worst-case scenario.'

Senior warrior of the Bulk Brigade: Together with warriors
who can defeat themselves.

Clea: Please tell me the location. I have received a request
from Lord Goat.

Senior warrior of the Bulk Brigade: The Forest of
Tranquility is the resting place of the past warriors.
Normally, even members of the Bulk Brigade are not allowed
to enter.

Clea: Even so, please tell me. I will not hesitate to choose
any means to save Lord Goat.

Senior warrior of the Bulk Brigade: As expected of warriors
recognized by Lord Goat, we were unable to do anything...
Please save him no matter what.

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Valt Region / Forest of
Tranquility\c[0]
Clea: What do you all think?

Thief Nora: I'm sure there was something that broke into the
room with the lingering scent of a beast!

Mage Relm: It could be the result of some kind of magic, but
honestly, I'm not a high-level mage.

Mage Relm: What caught my attention was the presence of a
book about the demons of nightmares. It's unclear whether
it's related to this incident or not...
Priestess Sophia: First, let's go to the tavern!

Priestess Sophia: Are you serious? If there really is a
werewolf, it should have become a rumor by now.

Bulk Corps warrior: The preparations for Stasis' escort are
complete!

Bulk Corps warrior: The preparations for Stasis' escort are
complete!

As senior warriors of the Bulk Brigade, we will be honored
to serve as escorts for all of you, who are the benefactors
of the Bulk Brigade, with Lord Goat at the forefront!
Clea: Yes, I will also participate.
Thief Nora: Is Sophia-san not coming?

Priestess Sophia: Yes, there is something that I am curious
about.
Mage Relm: It's probably about alcohol. Let's go ahead.

Priestess Sophia: Well then, let's wait for Stasis-san at
the tavern.

Priestess Sophia: It's true that werewolves exist, as I
witnessed a person transforming into a werewolf right before
my eyes!

Priestess Sophia: I can't believe it was the person
themselves...

Clea: It would be good if we could figure out where they
went...

Thief Nora: Leave it to me! If it smells the same as the
beast scent in the room, I should be able to track it!

Mage Relm: Let's go and find out what kind of magic turned
them into a werewolf!

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Valt Region / Abandoned Castle
of the Aspida Alliance\c[0]

Goat of the Bulk Gang: 'Nnngh! You're quite skilled, aren't
you!'

Shimosu of the Unknown Night: 'We used to fight each other
in the past, didn't we? Compared to back then, it seems like
your skills have declined, haven't they?'

Goat of the Bulk Gang: We were holding back against the
comrades who saved our lives, but it seems like it's fine
even if we lose an arm.

Shimosu of the Unknown Night: You're surprisingly kind. I've
decided to take your head back with me!

Shimosu of the Unknown Night: Don't interfere in a fight
between men--
Priestess Sophia: Do you understand the current situation?

Shimosu of the Unknown Night: Well, I guess it's like a test
of strength...
Priestess Sophia: Do you understand the current situation?

Shimosu of the Unknown Night: S-Sorry! Why is it that only
strong women gather around here...?

Goat of the Bulk Gang: Hahaha, as expected, Shimosu of the
Unknown Night is also powerless!
Goat of the Bulk Gang: W-What, me too!?

Priestess Sophia: I'm about to tell you something very
important. Can you please listen without making a fuss,
causing a commotion, or moving?
Priestess Sophia: You can do something like that, right?

Goat of the Bulk Gang: So you guys have your reasons, huh?
In terms of not choosing our opponents, you guys are even
more relentless than us!
Clea: You didn't explain the situation at all...

Shimosu of the Unknown Night: For now, she said to bring
someone strong.

Priestess Sophia: Unlike the others, I have become quite
emotionally involved in this situation.

Priestess Sophia: At the same time... I don't think Caron
can lead the empire in the right direction.
Priestess Sophia: Please... I beg for your cooperation.

Goat of the Bulk Gang: Our ancestors fought against the
empire, considering them as enemies, in order to protect the
Vault.

Goat of the Bulk Gang: That Vault has been swallowed by the
empire and is now part of the Fotizona Empire.

Goat of the Bulk Gang: Reclaiming the throne means rebelling
against the empire.
Priestess Sophia: That may be true... however,

Goat of the Bulk Gang: Hahaha, isn't this the best! We can
defeat the empire for the sake of the empire!

Goat of the Bulk Gang: Above all, our ancestors would be
pleased, and you are the benefactors of the Bulk Gang.

Goat of the Bulk Gang: Whether they are humans, monsters, or
dragons, this is a great opportunity to prove that the
strongest warriors are members of the Bulk Gang who never
back down!

Simos of the Unknown Night: You talk big, don't you? Let's
decide who's the strongest right now.

Clea: Thank you very much. I am proud to be able to fight
alongside the warriors of the Bulk Gang.

Goat of the Bulk Gang: Shall we also express our gratitude
to the goddesses Actina and Imiserinos, who can repay our
debts to you all!
